Is he more mad, who that child-cottage raises? Then add the murders of this fond desire, And with the sword provoke the madding fire. When jealous Marius late his mistress slew, And from a precipice himself he threw‚ VVas he not mad? or can you by your rule Condemn the mu'rderer, and acquit the fool? But though in civil phrase you change the name, Hadman and fool for ever arethe same. With hands clean wash'd, a sober, ancient wight Ran praying through the streets at early light, ‘⁶ Snatch me from death ; grant me alone to live: No mighty boon3 with ease the gods can give.” Sound were his senses; yet. if he were sold, His master sure this weakness must have told, And, if not fond a law-suit to mammio, Must have consess'd the slave unsound of brain. This crowd is by the doctrine of our schools Enroll’d in the large family of fools.
